# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

An Actor-RTC EchoService workload package with generated code isolated under `src/generated/`.

## Quick start

```bash
# 1. Create manifest.lock.toml
actr deps install

# 2. Regenerate src/generated/ from the local proto definition
actr gen -l rust

# 3. Build and package the workload
actr build
```

## How it works

- `protos/local/echo.proto` defines the `EchoService` interface.
- `actr init` only creates stable user-editable files and package metadata.
- `src/generated/` is created exclusively by `actr gen -l rust`.
- `src/echo_service.rs` is the protected user-code area for your business logic.
- `actr build` compiles the cdylib workload and packages it into a signed `.actr` archive.

## Customizing

Implement your own echo logic by modifying `EchoServiceImpl::echo` in `src/echo_service.rs`:

```rust
async fn echo(&self, request: EchoRequest) -> ActorResult<EchoResponse> {
    // Replace with your business logic
    Ok(EchoResponse { reply: request.message })
}
```
